                  <handDesc>

                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CJN006#ms_i1 #ms_i3">
                        <seg type="script">A mid-19th- to early 20th-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Titles and incipits of the psalms and other texts; numbers
                          of psalms and other texts; punctuation marks;
                        name of God, Mary; single letters and words.</seg>
                         <date notBefore="1850" notAfter="1930">.</date>
                         <desc>Slender rounded script, irregular
                           (size and slant change throughout the manuscript).
                           The vowel markers of the 5th order are bulky,
                           open. ም and ሞ look similar (both tend to a direct line),
                           in many cases not easy to distinguish. </desc>
                        <desc/>
                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CJN006#ms_i6">
                      <seg type="script">A script of a somewhat later
                        period, possibly late 19th or early 20th century.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1850" notAfter="1930"/>
                         <desc>Broad, rectangular; downstrokes are very broad.
                           Irregular, crudely written.
                           The vowel markers of the 5th order are bulky, open.</desc>
                        <desc/>
                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CJN006#a1">
                      <seg type="script">A 20th-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1900" notAfter="1975"/>
                         <desc>Crude, broadly spaced, strongly slanted; reddish brown ink used
                         for rubrication.</desc>
                         <note/>
                        <desc/>
                        </handNote>

                        <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CJN006#a2">
